Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.83,0:23:54.33,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,The day starts early for a trash game hunter.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.71,0:23:57.21,Sign_Basic,sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,900)\fnTimes New Roman\c&H000000&\3c&HFFFFFF&\shad0\b1\bord3.75}Why are you up so early?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.25,0:23:58.75,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,{\an8}I'm heading out into the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.75,0:24:00.38,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,so I needed to catch the first train.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.84,0:24:02.92,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,As the trash game hunter \Ntakes the maglev line west
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.92,0:24:06.09,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,he watches the scenery out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.09,0:24:08.55,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,Mr. Sunraku's gaze is focused.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.55,0:24:10.05,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,I got a tip that there's a shop
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.05,0:24:14.98,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,with an unopened copy of the limited \Nedition {\i1}Moody Music Adventure{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.98,0:24:17.27,Sign_Basic,sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,900)\fnTimes New Roman\c&H000000&\3c&HFFFFFF&\shad0\b1\bord3.75}What is {\i1}Moody Music Adventure{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.27,0:24:21.90,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,You know how modern VR games \Nare generally soundless?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.90,0:24:24.86,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,That is to say, they mostly don't use BGM?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.86,0:24:26.82,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,But there are also quite \Na few full-dive VR games
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.82,0:24:29.03,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,that use BGM as seen in the display copies.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.03,0:24:30.99,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,Put simply, most people \Nfind it annoying and end up
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.99,0:24:32.83,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,lowering the volume or turning off the BGM,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.83,0:24:34.95,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,but this one's a mix between \Nrhythm game and action RPG,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.95,0:24:37.29,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,and someone had the crazy idea to not \Nlet you turn the BGM volume down.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.29,0:24:38.71,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,So it's this trash game where you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.71,0:24:40.29,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,have to do rhythm game stuff \Nwith this really annoying BGM.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.29,0:24:42.75,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,The limited edition comes packaged \Nwith the main character's headphones.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.75,0:24:45.46,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,That nice and all, but who'd \Nwant to wear the headphones you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.46,0:24:48.13,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,associate with this BGM \Nthat gives you a headache?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.13,0:24:52.85,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,As he speaks on with the \Nforce of a raging bonfire,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.85,0:24:58.89,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,there is a bitterness in his tone, \Ncombined with a strange sense of delight.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.81,0:25:03.36,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,After getting a brief \Nbreakfast at the station,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.36,0:25:05.53,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,he arrives at the shop in question.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.53,0:25:08.65,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,But his eyes are harsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.03,0:25:11.53,Sign_Basic,sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(960,900)\fnTimes New Roman\c&H000000&\3c&HFFFFFF&\shad0\b1\bord3.75}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.24,0:25:11.53,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,{\an8}Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.99,0:25:13.49,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,It's a folding chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.12,0:25:15.70,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,It's still warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.70,0:25:17.16,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,Have they been here since \Nbefore the first train?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.12,0:25:21.42,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,This is the sign of a \Ncrazy trash game hunter.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.75,0:25:25.55,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,With his hand to the lingering \Nwarmth upon the folding chair,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.55,0:25:29.09,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,Mr. Sunraku scours the area around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.38,0:25:32.80,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,There's no way there are two limited \Nedition unopened copies in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.39,0:25:34.51,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.89,0:25:38.93,Default,Rakuro,0,0,0,,The moment the shop opens, \Nwe'll have to both run for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.35,0:25:43.27,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,Trash game—it refers to the \Ncontent of the game itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.27,0:25:48.94,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,Mr. Sunraku undergoes a focused warm-up \Nroutine as his eyes gaze ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.57,0:25:51.99,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,At times, he must even fight his own kind...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.99,0:25:55.37,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,But there's a smile on his lips.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.70,0:25:58.33,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,So, how'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.75,0:26:00.04,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,You get into a brawl?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.04,0:26:01.04,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,Nah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.04,0:26:03.88,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,The person was there for \Nsomething totally different.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.88,0:26:07.21,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,So it wasn't a crazy trash game hunter, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.55,0:26:11.51,Default,Sunraku,0,0,0,,What do you mean, "crazy trash game hunter"?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.18,0:26:14.97,Default,Oikatzo,0,0,0,,Please don't ask me that.
